<div1 type="letter">

<note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
<note type="curatorial">23</note>

<opener>
<address>
<addrLine>225 Willard Way, Ithaca, N.Y.</addrLine>
</address>
<dateline>May 27, 1960</dateline>
</opener>

<p>Dear John: &#8212; Ten copies of your Easter poem arrived. Thank you so much. I shall not hurry with their distribution, but as I run across people who would appreciate your poetry, I shall give one. I hope to make as many fans for you as I have <unclear/>. You see, your poetry is so wonderful to me, so helpful to the inner life of me, that I would share it.</p>

<p>How good that Alice &amp; the girls are back at Skyrim and that the plans once more alive with laughter and loveliness. I know that you are happy to have them with you and to be living once more in your own home with its dear <unclear/></p>

<p>This is only a brief message. But we are very <unclear>busy &amp; we</unclear> leave Tuesday for Hawaii. On return the latter part of August, I should be in Columbia for two or three days &amp; shall be certain to pay you a visit.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Always with my affection,</salute>
<signed>Slade</signed>
</closer>

</div1>
